(firstQuint)Comparison of Thermometry in Canada for Pediatrics.

 This study is designed as a multi-center study.

 This study will involve collecting temperatures on patients using the InstaTemp MD(R) device and the traditional method used in the clinical setting.

 Reliability and agreement of the InstaTemp MD(R) will be compared to the current Canadian Paediatric Society's definitely recommended methods of temperature measurement in certain age cohorts of infants and children.

